{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YDxsoYLYCK9ccokhgQ2fjL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Ralph Fix Plan\n     2→\n     3→## High Priority (Bugs)\n     4→\n     5→- [ ] #2 - Replace unsafe `unwrap()` calls with proper error handling in `src/gui/routes.rs`\n     6→  - Lines 207, 219, 231, 248: `serde_json::to_value(result).unwrap()` in analyze endpoints\n     7→  - Lines 597-598: `s.buffer.as_ref().unwrap()` and `s.file_path.as_ref().unwrap()` in `clean_file`\n     8→  - Replace with `map_err` returning `(StatusCode::INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR, ...)`\n     9→- [ ] #7 - Fix temp file memory leak from `Box::leak()` in `src/gui/routes.rs`\n    10→  - Line 169: `Box::leak(tmp_path.to_path_buf().into_boxed_path())` in `upload_file`\n    11→  - Line 555: `std::mem::forget(tmp_path)` in `clean_file`\n    12→  - Store temp paths in `AppState` so they get cleaned up when state is dropped\n    13→\n    14→## High Priority (Code Quality)\n    15→\n    16→- [ ] #4 - Replace `println!/eprintln!` with structured logging (tracing crate)\n    17→  - At minimum: `src/gui/mod.rs` line 46 uses `println!`\n    18→  - Scan entire codebase for println/eprintln and replace with `tracing::info!`/`tracing::error!`\n    19→\n    20→## Medium Priority (Features - Backend)\n    21→\n    22→- [ ] #6 - Expose FLAC and AAC format support in CLI\n    23→  - Check if symphonia already decodes these; add encoder support if missing\n    24→  - Update CLI help text and format detection in `src/audio/io.rs`\n    25→- [ ] #12 - Add `--dry-run` flag to clean command\n    26→  - Add flag to CLI args in `src/cli/`\n    27→  - Run detection/analysis but skip writing output file\n    28→- [ ] #13 - Add export report feature (JSON and PDF)\n    29→  - JSON export of analysis + cleaning results\n    30→  - PDF can be deferred if no easy crate available\n    31→- [ ] #19 - Add streaming support for large audio files\n    32→  - Chunked reading/processing to avoid loading entire file into memory\n    33→\n    34→## Medium Priority (Features - GUI)\n    35→\n    36→- [ ] #1 - Add spectrogram visualization for cleaned audio\n    37→  - Backend: add `/api/spectrogram/cleaned` endpoint (similar to `/api/waveform/cleaned`)\n    38→  - Frontend: render cleaned spectrogram alongside original\n    39→- [ ] #5 - Add upload progress indicator and file size validation\n    40→  - Frontend: show upload progress bar, validate max file size before upload\n    41→  - Backend: already has 500MB limit, surface it to frontend\n    42→- [ ] #10 - Display verification results and quality scores in GUI\n    43→- [ ] #11 - Add configuration and preset selection UI\n    44→- [ ] #14 - Add audio playback controls in GUI\n    45→- [ ] #9 - Add before/after audio comparison timeline\n    46→- [ ] #20 - Add detailed metadata tag viewer in GUI\n    47→\n    48→## Low Priority (Infrastructure)\n    49→\n    50→- [ ] #3 - Implement comprehensive test suite\n    51→  - Unit tests for detection modules, sanitization pipeline, DSP primitives\n    52→  - Integration tests for CLI commands\n    53→- [ ] #16 - Add React error boundaries for component crashes\n    54→- [ ] #8 - Add session persistence across page refreshes\n    55→- [ ] #17 - Add code coverage reporting (CI)\n    56→- [ ] #15 - Add release artifact publishing on git tags (CI)\n    57→- [ ] #18 - Optimize spectral operations to reuse STFT computations\n    58→\n    59→## Completed\n    60→- [x] Project enabled for Ralph\n    61→\n    62→## Working Notes\n    63→- All issues sourced from GitHub issues list (as of 2026-03-10)\n    64→- Issues labeled `ralph-task`: #2, #3, #4, #6, #7, #12, #15, #16, #17, #18\n    65→- After completing an issue, run `gh issue close <number>` to close it\n    66→- Always run `cargo check --all-targets && cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings && cargo fmt --all --check` before committing\n    67→- Commit format: conventional commits, single line, no co-authorship trailers\n    68→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9bd7957-c8f2-4e48-8fcc-7059d242854c","uuid":"acdfedf6-9b08-4b91-98bb-d1890b069e46","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/captain/code/github.com/polez/.ralph/fix_plan.md","content":"# Ralph Fix Plan\n\n## High Priority (Bugs)\n\n- [ ] #2 - Replace unsafe `unwrap()` calls with proper error handling in `src/gui/routes.rs`\n  - Lines 207, 219, 231, 248: `serde_json::to_value(result).unwrap()` in analyze endpoints\n  - Lines 597-598: `s.buffer.as_ref().unwrap()` and `s.file_path.as_ref().unwrap()` in `clean_file`\n  - Replace with `map_err` returning `(StatusCode::INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR, ...)`\n- [ ] #7 - Fix temp file memory leak from `Box::leak()` in `src/gui/routes.rs`\n  - Line 169: `Box::leak(tmp_path.to_path_buf().into_boxed_path())` in `upload_file`\n  - Line 555: `std::mem::forget(tmp_path)` in `clean_file`\n  - Store temp paths in `AppState` so they get cleaned up when state is dropped\n\n## High Priority (Code Quality)\n\n- [ ] #4 - Replace `println!/eprintln!` with structured logging (tracing crate)\n  - At minimum: `src/gui/mod.rs` line 46 uses `println!`\n  - Scan entire codebase for println/eprintln and replace with `tracing::info!`/`tracing::error!`\n\n## Medium Priority (Features - Backend)\n\n- [ ] #6 - Expose FLAC and AAC format support in CLI\n  - Check if symphonia already decodes these; add encoder support if missing\n  - Update CLI help text and format detection in `src/audio/io.rs`\n- [ ] #12 - Add `--dry-run` flag to clean command\n  - Add flag to CLI args in `src/cli/`\n  - Run detection/analysis but skip writing output file\n- [ ] #13 - Add export report feature (JSON and PDF)\n  - JSON export of analysis + cleaning results\n  - PDF can be deferred if no easy crate available\n- [ ] #19 - Add streaming support for large audio files\n  - Chunked reading/processing to avoid loading entire file into memory\n\n## Medium Priority (Features - GUI)\n\n- [ ] #1 - Add spectrogram visualization for cleaned audio\n  - Backend: add `/api/spectrogram/cleaned` endpoint (similar to `/api/waveform/cleaned`)\n  - Frontend: render cleaned spectrogram alongside original\n- [ ] #5 - Add upload progress indicator and file size validation\n  - Frontend: show upload progress bar, validate max file size before upload\n  - Backend: already has 500MB limit, surface it to frontend\n- [ ] #10 - Display verification results and quality scores in GUI\n- [ ] #11 - Add configuration and preset selection UI\n- [ ] #14 - Add audio playback controls in GUI\n- [ ] #9 - Add before/after audio comparison timeline\n- [ ] #20 - Add detailed metadata tag viewer in GUI\n\n## Low Priority (Infrastructure)\n\n- [ ] #3 - Implement comprehensive test suite\n  - Unit tests for detection modules, sanitization pipeline, DSP primitives\n  - Integration tests for CLI commands\n- [ ] #16 - Add React error boundaries for component crashes\n- [ ] #8 - Add session persistence across page refreshes\n- [ ] #17 - Add code coverage reporting (CI)\n- [ ] #15 - Add release artifact publishing on git tags (CI)\n- [ ] #18 - Optimize spectral operations to reuse STFT computations\n\n## Completed\n- [x] Project enabled for Ralph\n\n## Working Notes\n- All issues sourced from GitHub issues list (as of 2026-03-10)\n- Issues labeled `ralph-task`: #2, #3, #4, #6, #7, #12, #15, #16, #17, #18\n- After completing an issue, run `gh issue close <number>` to close it\n- Always run `cargo check --all-targets && cargo clippy --all-targets -- -D warnings && cargo fmt --all --check` before committing\n- Commit format: conventional commits, single line, no co-authorship trailers\n","numLines":68,"startLine":1,"totalLines":68}}}
